    <item>
      <title>Re: Returning after a few years</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=237869#M237869</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I still check out the creation guides from Caster's Realm from time to time.&amp;nbsp; Part of what I really like about them is comparing the various races.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Stats are much easier to obtain nowadays, maxing out wis and int is so easy that I generally don't put more than a few points when I create a new caster.&amp;nbsp; I do, however, stick a few in str and sta so that they can carry a bit more loot.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;So basically, other than giving you a bit of a jump start up to 30-35, I wouldn't overly obsess over where to put points.&amp;nbsp; You'll be fine, even if you go deliberately out of the way to give yourself the worst start ever.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I would, however, give some thought to deity selection.&amp;nbsp; It used to be that there were basically no positives to having a deity.&amp;nbsp; Then we started having deity specific cultural armors (which are mostly outgrown now and we have agnostic armors as well) and it seems to me that we have more deity restricted items than we used to.&amp;nbsp; Cultural tradeskills can also be impacted, although even half-elves have finally developed some culture of their own.&amp;nbsp; Fletching, for example, is a much easier and cheaper skill above 260 if you are a Tunarean Wood Elf simply because of their cultural recipes.&amp;nbsp; Warning though, this could change at any moment with or without warning.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
