    <item>
      <title>Re: Returning after a few years</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=237865#M237865</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The basics are still teh same, yes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Main differences to a person returning from days of old...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You will start in Gloomingdeep, a tutorial zone (you can opt out of this, but I wouldn't). Follow the tutorial to get pretty well caught up. We now have charm slots, and the reward from your first 'Hail Person X' quest results in a really nice charm for that slot.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The tutorial will let you get to level 10, and give you really basic gear to work with. When you leave the tutorial, you will be sent to the Plan of Knowledge (PoP zone that has become the default gathering spot, in case its been a whole lot of years).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A quest you recieve when you zone in will send you to an NPC in the Library. Hail her a few times and you can get 4 or 5 other quests that all take place there in PoK, and gets you familiarized with the zone. There are three NPCs in PoK that will give you newbie armor quests at each level after 10. This is in addition to the newbie armor quests available in your home city.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Your home city: Aside from possibly a few spell purchases, or cultural tradeskilling\tribute\etc, you never actually HAVE to go there. You do still start out with your Guild Note, and can head there and give it to your city's Guild master, but you don't have to.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Froglocks are the newest race, and Bezerkers are the newest class. I'm not sure how up to date your guides are, so just in case: Trolls are back in Grobb, and the froggies have an encampment out in the swamp somewhere. If you choose one of those races, be careful you don't head to the wrong home city.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;With the newer gear, initial stats mean less and less. By the time you hit 50 or so, you should easily be able to cap out your primary stats, and get real close on the rest. Agility seems to be the hardest for me to cap, personally.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In short, there are TONS of changes, but the tutorial will help you out on the ones that are game mechanics. The rest you really will just have to figure out as you come across them. You will be auo joined to a New Players channel, so help is mostly a /1 HELP! away.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Stromm supposedly has the most low level\new players, but I am not sure if that is by much of a margin.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you end up on 7th Hammer, look for any Klan ov da Grok members on line....they are all mostly me these days. I'll see if I can't get ya situated and answered.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
